# Mana · the resource · the land

a concept of the MTG (MTG Arena) game-world — emergence: natural. moniker ⟦Mana:MTG:188e9d⟧

**who —** Mana — the five-coloured (plus colourless) resource you spend to cast everything, drawn mostly from lands.
**what —** The economy of the game: tap lands for mana, climb the ‘curve,’ and balance the agony of too few or too many lands (‘mana screw’ and ‘flood’).
**where —** Under every spell, in every opening hand.
**why —** Because Magic's central tension is resources over time — the land you draw decides the game as much as the spells.
**how —** By lands tapped for coloured mana, a curve of costs, and the eternal gamble of the mana base.

**the seal —** I am the land turned to power — too little of me and you're screwed, too much and you flood; the whole game balances on me.

